<!--To develop a responsive Company Member Team Page using HTML and CSS, I'll provide a step-by-step guide, including a sample code for HTML and CSS. Since I can't view the "designed-1" file, I'll create a general structure for a team page that you can adjust according to the provided design reference.

HTML Structure
First, let's set up the HTML structure for the team page.-->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Company Member Team Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Our Team</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="team-members">
            <div class="member">
                <img src="member1.jpg" alt="Member 1">
                <h2>John Doe</h2>
                <p>CEO</p>
                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="member">
                <img src="member2.jpg" alt="Member 2">
                <h2>Jane Smith</h2>
                <p>CTO</p>
                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- Add more members as needed -->
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
<!--Explanation
HTML Structure:

The HTML document starts with a standard <!DOCTYPE html> declaration.
The head section includes meta tags for character set and viewport settings, and a link to the external CSS file.
The body section includes a header with the page title and a main section containing team members in a section element.-->
/**CSS Styles
Next, let's create a CSS file (styles.css) to style the team page and ensure responsiveness.*/

/* General Styles */
/* General Styles */
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem 0;
}

h1 {
    margin: 0;
}

/* Team Section Styles */
.team-members {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 2rem;
}

.member {
    background-color: white;
    margin: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    max-width: 300px;
    text-align: center;
}

.member img {
    border-radius: 50%;
    max-width: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

/* Responsiveness */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .team-members {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }
}

/* CSS Styles:

Basic styles for the body, header, and h1 tag to set the font, margin, padding, background color, and text color.
The .team-members class uses flexbox to arrange the team members. It ensures the layout is flexible and responsive.
Each .member class is styled with a white background, some padding, margin, border-radius for rounded corners, and a box-shadow for a subtle shadow effect.
The img tag inside .member is styled to be circular and centered with some margin at the bottom.
Media queries ensure that on smaller screens (max-width: 768px), the .team-members flex direction changes to column for better readability on mobile devices.*/

